def label_5_to_3(x):
  if x=='Extremely Positive':
    return 'Positive'
  elif x== 'Extremely Negative':
    return 'Negative'
  else:
    return x

import re
def pre_process(x):
    text=x
    output=re.sub("@\S+", " ", text)
    output=re.sub("https*\S+", " ", output)
    output = email_preprocess = re.sub(r"[^a-zA-Z]"," ",output)
    output = re.sub(r'\b\w{1,2}\b', '', output)   # removing the words length less than 2
    output =output.lower()                        # changing the words into lower case
    output = re.sub(' +', ' ',output)             # removing the extra space between the words
    return output

embeddings_dict = {}
with open("/content/drive/MyDrive/corona_NLP/glove.6B/glove.6B.50d.txt", 'r',encoding='utf8',errors='replace') as f:  
    for line in f:
        values = line.split()
        word = values[0]
        vector = np.asarray(values[1:], "float32")
        embeddings_dict[word] = vector
print(len(embeddings_dict))

In [91]:
embedding_matrix = np.zeros((len(t.word_index) + 1,50))
for word, i in t.word_index.items():
    embedding_vector = embeddings_dict.get(word)
    if embedding_vector is not None:
        # words not found in embedding index will be all-zeros.
        embedding_matrix[i] = embedding_vector
print(len(embedding_matrix))

Callbacks:¶

In [93]:
class Metrics(Callback):
    def on_train_begin(self, logs={}):
        self.val_f1s = []
    def on_epoch_end(self, epoch, logs={}):
        val_predict = (np.asarray(self.model.predict(validation_data[0]))).round()
        val_targ = validation_data[1]
        _val_f1 = f1_score(val_targ, val_predict,average='micro')
        self.val_f1s.append(_val_f1)
        print ("  val_f1: %f " %(_val_f1))
        return

log_directory   ="logs/fit/" + datetime.datetime.now().strftime("%Y%m%d-%H%M%S")
tensorboard_callback= tf.keras.callbacks.TensorBoard(log_dir=log_directory,histogram_freq=1,write_graph=True,write_grads=True)
earlystop = EarlyStopping(monitor='accuracy', patience=2, verbose=1)
metrics=Metrics() #f1 score
filepath         = "assignment_model_save/weights-{epoch:02d}-{val_accuracy:.4f}.hdf5"  # path for saving model
checkpoint       = ModelCheckpoint(filepath=filepath, monitor='val_accuracy', verbose=1,save_best_only=True, mode='max')
callback_list = [tensorboard_callback,earlystop,metrics,checkpoint]
validation_data=(after_pading_val_text, y_val_label)

model1 = Sequential()
